  "body": "See context from the 3rd AMA [here](https://www.reddit.com/r/ethereum/comments/ez972u/ama_we_are_the_eth_20_research_team_pt_3/fglqkfi/). The problem is that if someone deposits 32 ETH and early on their balance goes down (even just a bit) then they will have to wait until their balance goes back up to 32.5 ETH (because of hysteresis) for the effective balance to become 32 ETH. This could incentivise some validators to make a second deposit which is not ideal.",
