    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "My biggest concern is that if I'm not online in my activation epoch, then I'm going to lose rewards for a long period of time. Given this concern, what about some additional logic that the effective balance cannot change within X epochs? I.e. if I was activated at epoch N, my effective balance cannot drop until epoch N+X? If I had any initial liveness issue and I resolved it in X/2  time, then I would be OK.  \r\n\r\nThat would allow some tolerance for first time activations without much change to the rest of the hysteresis effective balance algorithm.",
