    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "There was a discussion about this on Discord.  @djrtwo if there is a true hysteresis on the downside then effective balance can be greater than balance.  I haven't thought it through, but could that cause problems?\r\n\r\nAn alternative was to go leave the existing system as is except to much reduce the hysteresis from requiring an additional 0.5 Ether before ticking up to requiring an additional 0.05 Ether.  This would maintain the current state where `effective balance <= balance` at all times, but much reduce the long-term penalty for dropping below an integer Ether boundary.",
